The Mode Dial


To select a shooting mode, rotate the dial until
the icon for the desired mode aligns with the
index.


ModeDescription
1 AUTO (AUTO)The camera automatically optimizes settings to the scene. You also have the option of choosing the desired scene mode yourself.48
2 P (PROGRAM AE)Aperture and shutter speed can be ad- justed using program shift.71
3 S (SHUTTER PRIORITY AE) A (APERTURE PRIORITY AE) M (MANUAL)Select for full control over camera set- tings, including aperture (M and A) and/or shutter speed (M and S).73 75 77
4 C1/C2/C3/C4 (CUSTOM 1/2/3/4)Take pictures using previously-stored settings.82
5 FILTER (FILTER)Take photos with filter effects.81
6 (MOVIE)Record movies.57
7 Vlog (Video blog)Record movies at settings suitable for vlogs (video blogs).58

| Mode | Description |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 AUTO (AUTO) | The camera automatically optimizes settings to the scene. You also have the option of choosing the desired scene mode yourself. | 48 |
| 2 P (PROGRAM AE) | Aperture and shutter speed can be ad- justed using program shift. | 71 |
| 3 S (SHUTTER PRIORITY AE) A (APERTURE PRIORITY AE) M (MANUAL) | Select for full control over camera set- tings, including aperture (M and A) and/or shutter speed (M and S). | 73 75 77 |
| 4 C1/C2/C3/C4 (CUSTOM 1/2/3/4) | Take pictures using previously-stored settings. | 82 |
| 5 FILTER (FILTER) | Take photos with filter effects. | 81 |
| 6 (MOVIE) | Record movies. | 57 |
| 7 Vlog (Video blog) | Record movies at settings suitable for vlogs (video blogs). | 58 |
